---
layout: base.njk
title: Research & References
---

<section class="intro">
    <h1>Research & References</h1>
    <p>A curated collection of external standards, proposals, and ecosystem libraries that influence the architectural decisions of Web Everything.</p>
</section>

{% if designRefs.length %}
<section style="margin-bottom: 3rem;">
    {#- Dogfood (#2103, #1607/#1820 Fork 1a): the design-references banner is a `<we-card>` frame with the
        shot-count as a `<we-badge>` — the same raw card+badge composition the sibling catalog tiles use
        (resources.njk, blocks.njk), correct with JS off via the `we-card{}`/`we-badge{}` SSR baseline in
        style.css and upgraded in place by the client CE (base.njk). (The #2098 `weCard` MACRO can't carry a
        nested `weBadge` — it would serialize the badge's own placeholder into the card's spec attribute, and
        the single-pass `weComponentSSR` transform never re-renders that inner placeholder; so a badge-bearing
        tile uses the raw-tag pattern, and the no-badge tiles below use the macro.) The whole-tile click stays
        on the OUTER `<a class="project-card">`; `.project-card:has(> we-card|.fui-card)` strips the anchor's
        own frame so the card is the sole box. -#}
    <a href="/research/design-references/" class="project-card" style="text-decoration: none; color: inherit; display: block;">
        <we-card>
            <div style="display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: space-between; gap: 1rem;">
                <div>
                    <h3 class="project-title" style="margin: 0 0 0.35rem 0;">Design Reference Library &rarr;</h3>
                    <p style="margin: 0; color: var(--color-text-muted); font-size: 0.9em;">A growing, deduplicated corpus of real web-<strong>app</strong> screenshots, captured with rich metadata for later analysis and codification.</p>
                </div>
                <we-badge tone="neutral">{{ designRefs.length }} shots</we-badge>
            </div>
        </we-card>
    </a>
</section>
{% endif %}

{% from "research-freshness.njk" import freshnessBadge %}
{% if researchTopics.length %}
<section style="margin-bottom: 3rem;">
    <h2 style="margin-bottom: 1rem;">Open Research Topics</h2>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 1.5rem; color: var(--color-text-muted); font-size: 0.9em;">Active investigations into design problems and architectural decisions.</p>
    <div class="project-grid">
        {# Refresh-as-new-report (#441 Fork 1 / #478): a refreshed topic publishes a new dated report +
           a new registry entry that supersedes the old one (which flips to status: superseded). The
           grid surfaces the *latest as canonical* — superseded revisions are demoted from here, still
           reachable via their own permalink and the canonical topic's revision-history chain. #}
        {#- Dogfood (#2103, #1607/#1820 Fork 1a): each topic tile is a `<we-card>` frame + status `<we-badge>`,
            the same raw card+badge composition as the sibling catalog tiles (blocks.njk, resources.njk). The
            status vocab maps to a shared tone — open→warning (amber), resolved→success (green), else→neutral —
            matching the prior hand-rolled swatch. Summary + freshness badge + tag chips stay in the body. Raw
            tags (not the #2098 macro) because the macro can't carry a nested badge; JS-off correct via the
            `we-card{}`/`we-badge{}` style.css baseline, upgraded in place by the client CE. The whole-tile
            click stays on the OUTER anchor; `.project-card:has(> we-card|.fui-card)` strips its own frame. -#}
        {% for topic in researchTopics %}
        {% if topic.status != 'superseded' %}
        {% set _topicTone = 'warning' if topic.status == 'open' else ('success' if topic.status == 'resolved' else 'neutral') %}
        <a href="/research/{{ topic.id }}/" class="project-card" style="text-decoration: none; color: inherit; display: block;">
            <we-card>
                <div class="project-header" style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem; display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: center; gap: 0.5rem;">
                    <h3 class="project-title" style="margin: 0;">{{ topic.title }}</h3>
                    <we-badge tone="{{ _topicTone }}">{{ topic.status | title }}</we-badge>
                </div>
                <p style="margin: 0 0 0.75rem 0; color: var(--color-text-muted); font-size: 0.9em;">{{ topic.summary }}</p>
                <div style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">{{ freshnessBadge(topic) }}</div>
                {% if topic.tags %}
                <div style="display: flex; gap: 0.35rem; flex-wrap: wrap;">
                    {% for tag in topic.tags %}
                    <span style="display: inline-block; padding: 0.1rem 0.5rem; border-radius: 9999px; background: var(--color-surface-alt, #f1f5f9); color: var(--color-text-muted, #475569); font-size: 0.75em;">{{ tag }}</span>
                    {% endfor %}
                </div>
                {% endif %}
            </we-card>
        </a>
        {% endif %}
        {% endfor %}
    </div>
</section>
{% endif %}

<h2 style="margin-bottom: 1rem;">External References</h2>
<div class="project-grid">
    {#- Dogfood (#2103, #1607/#1820 Fork 1a): each External-References category is a `<we-card>` content tile
        (not an anchor — the link list lives inside the body). Raw tag (not the #2098 macro) kept consistent
        with the tiles above and round-trip-safe (a `link.title`/`context` carrying encoded markup would leak
        through the macro's `innerHTML` body path). `category` → the card heading; description + the `<ul>` of
        external links stay in the body. `.project-card:has(> we-card|.fui-card)` strips the wrapper frame so
        the card is the sole box; the client CE upgrades it in place (JS-off correct via the style.css
        baseline). -#}
    {% for section in references %}
    <div class="project-card" style="display: block; height: auto;">
        <we-card>
            <div class="project-header" style="margin-bottom: 1rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border); padding-bottom: 0.5rem;">
                <h2 class="project-title" style="margin: 0;">{{ section.category }}</h2>
            </div>
            <p style="margin-bottom: 1.5rem; color: var(--color-text-muted); font-size: 0.9em;">{{ section.description }}</p>
            <ul style="list-style: none; padding: 0; margin: 0;">
                {% for link in section.links %}
                <li style="margin-bottom: 1rem;">
                    <a href="{{ link.url }}" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="font-weight: 600; text-decoration: none; color: var(--color-primary); display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.5rem;">
                        {{ link.title }}
                        <svg style="width: 14px; height: 14px; opacity: 0.5;" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M10 6H6a2 2 0 00-2 2v10a2 2 0 002 2h10a2 2 0 002-2v-4M14 4h6m0 0v6m0-6L10 14"></path></svg>
                    </a>
                    {% if link.context %}
                    <p style="margin: 0.25rem 0 0 0; font-size: 0.85em; color: var(--color-text-muted);">{{ link.context }}</p>
                    {% endif %}
                </li>
                {% endfor %}
            </ul>
        </we-card>
    </div>
    {% endfor %}
</div>
